7, 6, 5,

31
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:52,760
4, 3, 2, 1, stop.

32
00:01:53,150 --> 00:01:55,310
1853276305770

33
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:56,760
- Correct?
- All correct!

34
00:01:56,760 --> 00:01:57,600
Correct!

35
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:00,150
Who brought a phone book?

36
00:02:00,150 --> 00:02:01,680
- A phone book.
- I have one!

37
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:03,000
Pick a random page for him.

38
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,400
How is his brain so sharp?

39
00:02:04,510 --> 00:02:06,070
Hurry up, test him with the phone book.

40
00:02:06,070 --> 00:02:06,910
Here.

41
00:02:07,510 --> 00:02:08,350
Get ready.

42
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:11,080
(Jiangxi Home; Chai Yilin; Math Teacher Miao)
5, 4, 3, 2, 1.

43
00:02:11,710 --> 00:02:13,080
Stop shaking, I can't see clearly.

44
00:02:13,080 --> 00:02:15,150
Wait. Last time there were 13 digits,

45
00:02:15,150 --> 00:02:16,120
but this time only 8.

46
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:18,400
We haven't told him
which one to memorize.

47
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,240
True.

48
00:02:19,280 --> 00:02:21,870
The first is 0793837018.

49
00:02:21,870 --> 00:02:24,310
The second is 67242279.

50
00:02:24,310 --> 00:02:26,680
The third is 62478339.

51
00:02:26,870 --> 00:02:28,310
- Is that right?
- All correct!

52
00:02:28,590 --> 00:02:29,560
All three memorized!

53
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:30,940
Amazing!

54
00:02:30,990 --> 00:02:32,030
I didn't remember anything.

55
00:02:32,030 --> 00:02:34,080
Chang Wuji, you only looked once,

56
00:02:34,080 --> 00:02:35,590
and you remembered over 20 numbers!

57
00:02:35,590 --> 00:02:37,000
Maybe I should donate my brain.

58
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,080
Chang Wuji,

59
00:02:38,080 --> 00:02:39,400
